üü¶ US ‚Äì Define returned quantity per accessory

User Story

As a coach
I want to define the quantity returned for each accessory
So that I can accurately declare multiple returned items of the same accessory type

‚∏ª

Description

On Step 2 ‚Äì Select Accessories, each accessory item provides quantity controls allowing the coach to specify how many units are returned.

For each accessory:
	‚Ä¢	A minus (-) button decreases the quantity
	‚Ä¢	A plus (+) button increases the quantity
	‚Ä¢	Quantity starts at 1 when the accessory is selected
	‚Ä¢	Quantity cannot be lower than 1

When an accessory is added to the Return Summary:
	‚Ä¢	If quantity = 1 ‚Üí no quantity indicator is displayed
	‚Ä¢	If quantity > 1 ‚Üí a quantity badge (e.g. x2, x3) is displayed on the accessory card

‚∏ª

Business Rules
	1.	Selection & quantity
	‚Ä¢	Selecting an accessory automatically sets its quantity to 1
	‚Ä¢	Unselecting an accessory removes it entirely from the Return Summary
	2.	Quantity constraints
	‚Ä¢	Minimum quantity: 1
	‚Ä¢	No upper limit (unless defined later by business rules)
	3.	Return Summary display
	‚Ä¢	Quantity badge is displayed only when quantity > 1
	‚Ä¢	The badge reflects the current quantity in real time

‚∏ª

Acceptance Criteria (Gherkin)

GIVEN I am on Step 2 "Select accessories"
WHEN I select an accessory
THEN its quantity is set to 1 by default

WHEN I click the "+" button
THEN the accessory quantity increases by 1

WHEN I click the "-" button
AND the quantity is greater than 1
THEN the accessory quantity decreases by 1

WHEN the quantity is 1
THEN the "-" button is disabled

WHEN an accessory quantity is greater than 1
THEN a quantity badge is displayed in the Return Summary

WHEN I unselect an accessory
THEN it is removed from the Return Summary regardless of quantity


‚∏ª

UX / Implementation Notes
	‚Ä¢	Quantity controls are visible only when the accessory is selected
	‚Ä¢	Quantity updates are reflected instantly in the Return Summary
	‚Ä¢	Recommended badge format: x2, x3, etc.
	‚Ä¢	Badge placement: top-right corner of the accessory card in Return Summary

‚∏ª

Business Value
	‚Ä¢	Supports real-world return scenarios (multiple chargers, badges, headsets, etc.)
	‚Ä¢	Improves accuracy of return declarations
	‚Ä¢	Avoids duplicate accessory entries
	‚Ä¢	Keeps the UI clean and scalable

